# Copy to routine-sync-repos.conf (same directory) and adjust.
# Format: clone_name|git_url_or_absolute_path|branch|src_subdir
#   clone_name   — directory name under $ROUTINE_SYNC_ROOT for remote clones (ignored for local paths)
#   branch       — always used: first clone checks out this ref; later `clone`/`pull`/`sync` stay on it
#   src_subdir   — relative to repo root; *.m files here are copied (default: src)
#
# Order matters: later rows win if two repos ship the same BASENAME.m into the destination.
#
# Remote (inside a container or build host) — orgs and branches can differ (vehu10_bootstrap default):
# data-loader|https://github.com/glilly/VistA-FHIR-Data-Loader.git|vaready-wd-compat|src
# server-codex|https://github.com/WorldVistA/VistA-FHIR-Server-Codex.git|master|src
#
# Local working copies (development host):
# data-loader|/home/you/VistA-FHIR-Data-Loader|vaready-wd-compat|src
# server-codex|/home/you/VistA-FHIR-Server-Codex|vaready-wd-compat|src
